.TH "LIGHTNING-TOWER" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-tower \- watchtower client + server (FEAT-186)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning tower
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning tower — watchtower client + server (FEAT-186).

Wraps clightning's `altruistwatchtower` (client) and
`watchtower` (server) plugins. BOLT-13 is still draft;
see share/doc/lightning/standards/README-drafts.md.

Subcommands:
  client-add <pubkey@host:port>     register a remote tower
  client-list                       registered towers
  client-stats                      sessions / breaches witnessed
  server-on                         enable watchtower role
  server-off                        disable
  server-status                     peers + breaches witnessed
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning tower <subcommand>

   client-add <pubkey@host:port>   register a remote tower
   client-list                     show registered towers
   client-stats                    sessions / breaches witnessed
   server-on                       enable watchtower-server role
   server-off                      disable
   server-status                   peers + breaches witnessed

The justice scenario: if your channel peer publishes a stale
commitment while you're offline, a registered tower watches
the chain on your behalf and broadcasts the penalty
transaction. See BOLT-3 \exc2\exa7revocation-keys and the
BOLT-13 draft for details.
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
